01:23:25,386 --> 01:23:27,386
and to the right of them a fork.

1936
01:23:27,386 --> 01:23:28,386
Next person, left of them

1937
01:23:28,386 --> 01:23:29,386
and right of them a fork.

1938
01:23:29,386 --> 01:23:33,386
And nobody knows whether to go for the left fork,

1939
01:23:33,386 --> 01:23:34,386
for the left fork,

1940
01:23:34,386 --> 01:23:36,386
or the right fork.

1941
01:23:36,386 --> 01:23:39,386
And they sit there, and they sit there,

1942
01:23:39,386 --> 01:23:40,386
and they sit there,

1943
01:23:40,386 --> 01:23:42,386
and they can't decide what to do,

1944
01:23:42,386 --> 01:23:44,386
until all of a sudden,

1945
01:23:44,386 --> 01:23:45,886
one of them makes a

1946
01:23:45,886 --> 01:23:47,386
little motion toward the right fork,

1947
01:23:47,386 --> 01:23:49,386
and then they all go for the right fork.

1948
01:23:49,386 --> 01:23:52,386
There was nothing asymmetric to begin with,

1949
01:23:52,386 --> 01:23:54,386
but there was a kind of instability.

1950
01:23:54,386 --> 01:23:56,386
There was a kind of instability,

1951
01:23:56,386 --> 01:24:00,386
two possibilities in instability,

1952
01:24:00,386 --> 01:24:02,386
and the instability being such

1953
01:24:02,386 --> 01:24:04,386
that when the instability is kicked in,

1954
01:24:04,386 --> 01:24:06,386
when it's kicked off,

1955
01:24:06,386 --> 01:24:08,386
the whole universe, so to speak,

1956
01:24:08,386 --> 01:24:11,386
suddenly goes one way instead of the other way.

1957
01:24:11,386 --> 01:24:16,386
So, I will give you an example,

1958
01:24:16,386 --> 01:24:20,386
a mathematical example.

1959
01:24:20,386 --> 01:24:23,386
A ferromagnet is an example

1960
01:24:23,386 --> 01:24:26,386
of spontaneous symmetry breaking.

1961
01:24:26,386 --> 01:24:29,386
But let's think, let's start with a very simple example.

1962
01:24:29,386 --> 01:24:32,386
The simple example is,

1963
01:24:34,386 --> 01:24:39,386
a bunch of spins,

1964
01:24:39,386 --> 01:24:43,386
and the spins can either be all up or all,

1965
01:24:43,386 --> 01:24:46,386
sorry, the spins can either be up or down.

1966
01:24:46,386 --> 01:24:49,386
For the moment, it's not even important

1967
01:24:49,386 --> 01:24:51,386
that we're talking about quantum mechanics.

1968
01:24:51,386 --> 01:24:56,386
These could be coins, classical coins.

1969
01:24:56,386 --> 01:25:01,386
And the coins can either be up or down.

1970
01:25:01,386 --> 01:25:04,386
They're laid out on a table,

1971
01:25:04,386 --> 01:25:08,386
in a lattice.

1972
01:25:08,386 --> 01:25:11,386
Here they are.

1973
01:25:11,386 --> 01:25:13,386
And there's an interaction energy

1974
01:25:13,386 --> 01:25:15,386
between neighboring coins.

1975
01:25:15,386 --> 01:25:17,386
The interaction energy is such

1976
01:25:17,386 --> 01:25:20,386
that if the coins, if the neighbors are opposite,

1977
01:25:20,386 --> 01:25:23,386
for example, a heads and a tails,

1978
01:25:23,386 --> 01:25:25,386
that costs energy.

1979
01:25:25,386 --> 01:25:27,386
In other words, there's some kind of force

1980
01:25:27,386 --> 01:25:31,386
between the particles, or the spins,

1981
01:25:31,386 --> 01:25:32,386
or the coins,

1982
01:25:32,386 --> 01:25:34,386
so that if they're opposite,

1983
01:25:34,386 --> 01:25:36,386
that costs some energy.

1984
01:25:36,386 --> 01:25:39,386
If they're parallel, it costs less energy.

1985
01:25:39,386 --> 01:25:42,386
So they like to be parallel.

1986
01:25:42,386 --> 01:25:44,386
Energetically, they like to be parallel.

1987
01:25:44,386 --> 01:25:47,386
But parallel can mean this way or this way.

1988
01:25:47,386 --> 01:25:50,386
Anti-parallel can mean this way or this way.

1989
01:25:50,386 --> 01:25:54,386
Anti-parallel costs more energy than parallel.

1990
01:25:54,386 --> 01:25:58,386
Now think about the state of lowest energy.

1991
01:25:58,386 --> 01:26:00,386
What is the state of lowest energy?

1992
01:26:00,386 --> 01:26:02,386
The state of lowest energy

1993
01:26:02,386 --> 01:26:04,386
is obviously,

1994
01:26:04,386 --> 01:26:10,386
all heads or all tails.

1995
01:26:10,386 --> 01:26:13,386
There are two states of lowest energy.

1996
01:26:13,386 --> 01:26:16,386
All heads or all tails.

1997
01:26:16,386 --> 01:26:18,386
Which one is the ground state?

1998
01:26:18,386 --> 01:26:20,386
They're both ground states.

1999
01:26:20,386 --> 01:26:24,386
But now, supposing way far away,

2000
01:26:24,386 --> 01:26:27,386
off a hundred miles away,

2001
01:26:27,386 --> 01:26:31,386
one of the spins is known to be heads.

2002
01:26:31,386 --> 01:26:33,386
That one is asymmetric.

2003
01:26:33,386 --> 01:26:36,386
Well, normally, under most circumstances,

2004
01:26:36,386 --> 01:26:38,386
you would say that one degree of freedom,

2005
01:26:38,386 --> 01:26:40,386
very, very far away,

2006
01:26:40,386 --> 01:26:42,386
has no effect

2007
01:26:42,386 --> 01:26:46,386
on what the properties of the ground state are

2008
01:26:46,386 --> 01:26:48,386
far away from that degree of freedom.

2009
01:26:48,386 --> 01:26:50,386
That's a typical expectation.

2010
01:26:50,386 --> 01:26:51,386
It's usually true.

2011
01:26:51,386 --> 01:26:53,386
It's almost always true, ordinarily.

2012
01:26:53,386 --> 01:26:56,386
But, in this case,

2013
01:26:56,386 --> 01:26:58,386
that one head

2014
01:26:58,386 --> 01:27:00,386
will cause the ground state energy

2015
01:27:00,386 --> 01:27:02,386
to be different if they're all heads

2016
01:27:02,386 --> 01:27:04,386
than if they're all tails.

2017
01:27:04,386 --> 01:27:06,386
If they're all heads,

2018
01:27:06,386 --> 01:27:09,386
then you'll save one unit of energy,

2019
01:27:09,386 --> 01:27:12,386
and so, in seeking its ground state,

2020
01:27:12,386 --> 01:27:15,386
this system will tend to all heads

2021
01:27:15,386 --> 01:27:17,386
rather than all tails.

2022
01:27:17,386 --> 01:27:19,386
Once it's all heads,

2023
01:27:19,386 --> 01:27:21,386
then you can forget,

2024
01:27:21,386 --> 01:27:24,386
you can, once it's all heads,

2025
01:27:29,386 --> 01:27:31,386
then you can start over again,

2026
01:27:31,386 --> 01:27:33,386
and say, look,

2027
01:27:33,386 --> 01:27:35,386
the lowest energy state of this system is all heads,

2028
01:27:35,386 --> 01:27:37,386
it will cost me some energy

2029
01:27:37,386 --> 01:27:39,386
to put a tail in there

2030
01:27:39,386 --> 01:27:41,386
because it has four neighbors

2031
01:27:41,386 --> 01:27:44,386
which are trying to make it a head.

2032
01:27:44,386 --> 01:27:47,386
So, the result is

2033
01:27:47,386 --> 01:27:49,386
that this kind of system,

2034
01:27:49,386 --> 01:27:51,386
although it started with a symmetry,

2035
01:27:51,386 --> 01:27:53,386
it started with a symmetry,

2036
01:27:53,386 --> 01:27:55,386
heads goes to tails,

2037
01:27:55,386 --> 01:27:59,386
asymptotically very, very far away,

2038
01:27:59,386 --> 01:28:01,386
boundary conditions,

2039
01:28:01,386 --> 01:28:04,386
or just a very, very distant degree of freedom,

2040
01:28:04,386 --> 01:28:07,386
will tip off a instability

2041
01:28:07,386 --> 01:28:11,386
and put the system into one of the many possible,

2042
01:28:11,386 --> 01:28:14,386
in this case, only two possible ground states,

2043
01:28:14,386 --> 01:28:16,386
and once it's in that ground state,

2044
01:28:16,386 --> 01:28:19,386
then the properties of what goes on in here

2045
01:28:19,386 --> 01:28:21,386
are determined by that ground state.

2046
01:28:21,386 --> 01:28:23,386
In particular,

2047
01:28:23,386 --> 01:28:25,386
a tail will cost you energy

2048
01:28:25,386 --> 01:28:28,386
because of the presence of all the heads.

2049
01:28:29,386 --> 01:28:31,386
This is the simple,

2050
01:28:31,386 --> 01:28:34,386
and the most primitive example

2051
01:28:34,386 --> 01:28:36,386
of a spontaneous symmetry breaking.

2052
01:28:36,386 --> 01:28:38,386
How is it different

2053
01:28:38,386 --> 01:28:41,386
than just an ordinary symmetry breaking?

2054
01:28:41,386 --> 01:28:44,386
What would an ordinary symmetry breaking mean?

2055
01:28:44,386 --> 01:28:47,386
An ordinary symmetry breaking,

2056
01:28:47,386 --> 01:28:50,386
or what we can call an explicit symmetry breaking,

2057
01:28:50,386 --> 01:28:52,386
would be a symmetry breaking

2058
01:28:52,386 --> 01:28:57,386
if heads had a different energy than tails.

2059
01:28:57,386 --> 01:29:00,386
Not pairwise energies,

2060
01:29:00,386 --> 01:29:02,386
but just one head by itself.

2061
01:29:02,386 --> 01:29:04,386
Supposing that one head by itself

2062
01:29:04,386 --> 01:29:07,386
had less energy than a tail,

2063
01:29:07,386 --> 01:29:09,386
then of course it would be completely obvious

2064
01:29:09,386 --> 01:29:10,386
that the system would,

2065
01:29:10,386 --> 01:29:12,386
in its lowest energy state,

2066
01:29:12,386 --> 01:29:14,386
be all heads.

2067
01:29:14,386 --> 01:29:17,386
And so it would be also the case,

2068
01:29:17,386 --> 01:29:19,386
all heads,

2069
01:29:19,386 --> 01:29:21,386
but there would be no second ground state

2070
01:29:21,386 --> 01:29:23,386
in which they were all tails.

2071
01:29:23,386 --> 01:29:26,386
It would be biased by the energy,

2072
01:29:26,386 --> 01:29:28,386
or be biased by the energy,

2073
01:29:28,386 --> 01:29:30,386
not the one extra point,

2074
01:29:30,386 --> 01:29:33,386
or the particle infinitely far away,

2075
01:29:33,386 --> 01:29:37,386
but by the local things going on nearby.

2076
01:29:37,386 --> 01:29:44,386
So that would be a biased situation

2077
01:29:44,386 --> 01:29:46,386
where heads and tails

2078
01:29:46,386 --> 01:29:48,386
were not equivalent to each other,

2079
01:29:48,386 --> 01:29:50,386
were not energetically the same,

2080
01:29:50,386 --> 01:29:52,386
and it's not a spontaneous symmetry breaking,

2081
01:29:52,386 --> 01:29:54,386
it's just no symmetry to begin with,

2082
01:29:54,386 --> 01:29:56,386
or an explicit symmetry breaking.

2083
01:29:56,386 --> 01:29:58,386
Is there any difference

2084
01:29:58,386 --> 01:30:00,386
between explicit symmetry breaking

2085
01:30:00,386 --> 01:30:02,386
and spontaneous symmetry breaking?

2086
01:30:02,386 --> 01:30:04,386
Yes, there is.

2087
01:30:04,386 --> 01:30:07,386
There is one phenomena that can happen

2088
01:30:07,386 --> 01:30:10,386
when there's spontaneous symmetry breaking

2089
01:30:10,386 --> 01:30:11,386
that will not happen

2090
01:30:11,386 --> 01:30:13,386
if there's explicit symmetry breaking.

2091
01:30:13,386 --> 01:30:16,386
The phenomena is called domain walls.

2092
01:30:16,386 --> 01:30:20,386
A domain wall is what happens

2093
01:30:20,386 --> 01:30:25,386
if far away out here,

2094
01:30:25,386 --> 01:30:27,386
very, very far away,

2095
01:30:27,386 --> 01:30:29,386
you insist along this line here

2096
01:30:29,386 --> 01:30:31,386
that everybody is heads,

2097
01:30:31,386 --> 01:30:32,386
and way out here,

2098
01:30:32,386 --> 01:30:36,386
you assume that everybody is tails.

2099
01:30:36,386 --> 01:30:39,386
What then is the state of lowest energy?

2100
01:30:39,386 --> 01:30:41,386
And then the state of lowest energy

2101
01:30:41,386 --> 01:30:44,386
is everybody on this side, tails,

2102
01:30:44,386 --> 01:30:46,386
everybody on this side, heads,

2103
01:30:46,386 --> 01:30:49,386
and a boundary in between

2104
01:30:49,386 --> 01:30:50,386
where heads go from,

2105
01:30:50,386 --> 01:30:54,386
where tails go from the boundary,

2106
01:30:54,386 --> 01:30:57,386
where you go from tails to heads,

2107
01:30:57,386 --> 01:30:59,386
called domain wall.

2108
01:30:59,386 --> 01:31:01,386
So the presence of domain wall,

2109
01:31:01,386 --> 01:31:02,386
and this would not be the case

2110
01:31:02,386 --> 01:31:04,386
if you had explicit symmetry breaking.

2111
01:31:04,386 --> 01:31:07,386
If you had explicit symmetry breaking,

2112
01:31:07,386 --> 01:31:10,386
then the state of lowest energy

2113
01:31:10,386 --> 01:31:12,386
would just be all heads, period.

2114
01:31:12,386 --> 01:31:13,386
Wouldn't care that,

2115
01:31:13,386 --> 01:31:14,386
wouldn't care very much

2116
01:31:14,386 --> 01:31:17,386
that you did this thing over here.

2117
01:31:17,386 --> 01:31:19,386
So spontaneous symmetry breaking,

2118
01:31:19,386 --> 01:31:20,386
in this case,

2119
01:31:20,386 --> 01:31:22,386
the signal of it

2120
01:31:22,386 --> 01:31:25,386
is the existence under certain circumstances,

2121
01:31:25,386 --> 01:31:28,386
certain kinds of experimental setups,

2122
01:31:28,386 --> 01:31:31,386
would lead to the existence of domain walls,

2123
01:31:31,386 --> 01:31:33,386
where on one side you had one thing,

2124
01:31:33,386 --> 01:31:35,386
on the other side you had the other thing.

2125
01:31:35,386 --> 01:31:38,386
And so it would be the presence of domain walls

2126
01:31:38,386 --> 01:31:40,386
which would be the signal

2127
01:31:40,386 --> 01:31:44,386
that there was a spontaneous symmetry breaking.

2128
01:31:44,386 --> 01:31:46,386
All right, so this is the basic idea

2129
01:31:46,386 --> 01:31:48,386
of spontaneous symmetry breaking,

2130
01:31:48,386 --> 01:31:50,386
a symmetry of the system,

2131
01:31:50,386 --> 01:31:52,386
but with an instability,

2132
01:31:52,386 --> 01:31:55,386
or an instability

2133
01:31:55,386 --> 01:31:57,386
that you can kick off

2134
01:31:57,386 --> 01:31:59,386
by going very far away

2135
01:31:59,386 --> 01:32:01,386
and just fiddling with something very far away,

2136
01:32:01,386 --> 01:32:05,386
and that will fix everything.

2137
01:32:05,386 --> 01:32:09,386
As I said, the signal or the signature of it

2138
01:32:09,386 --> 01:32:12,386
is the existence of domain walls.

2139
01:32:12,386 --> 01:32:14,386
Next time we'll talk about other kinds

2140
01:32:14,386 --> 01:32:16,386
of spontaneous symmetry breaking

2141
01:32:16,386 --> 01:32:20,386
and come to the Higgs phenomenon.

2142
01:32:20,386 --> 01:32:23,386
The Higgs phenomenon is a phenomenon

2143
01:32:23,386 --> 01:32:25,386
of spontaneous symmetry breaking,

2144
01:32:25,386 --> 01:32:26,386
and we'll talk about it next time.

2145
01:32:26,386 --> 01:32:27,386
So,

2146
01:32:27,386 --> 01:32:31,386
just keep this example in mind.

2147
01:32:32,386 --> 01:32:36,386
For more, please visit us at stanford.edu.

